external_knowledge:
- Low patient readmission rates refer to rates less than 0.15 (15%); 
- Long-established hospitals refer to hospitals established over 20 years ago (7305 days); 
- Approved safety reports are compliance reports with a report type of 'Safety' and an approval status of 'approved'.

- "raked in more than their fair share of revenue" refers to hospitals with average total revenue greater than the median average total revenue across all hospitals; 
- "patient satisfaction scores" and "readmission rates" are indicators of the quality of care provided by hospitals; 
- "year 2023" is the specific time frame of interest for the patient outcomes.

sql:
SELECT income_level, COUNT(*) AS patient_count
FROM patient_demographics
GROUP BY income_level;
